description: The screenshot displays a standard Windows XP desktop with a solid blue background. The Start button is visible in the bottom left corner, and the system tray with the time (11:04 AM) is in the bottom right corner. A white mouse cursor, angled slightly upward, is positioned in the center of the screen. The "Recycle Bin" icon is located on the right side of the desktop. No other windows or applications appear to be open or active.

The screenshot shows the Windows XP desktop with the Start menu open. The "Control Panel" option within the Start menu is highlighted, indicating the user's mouse is hovering over it. The rest of the desktop, including the position of the Recycle Bin and the time in the system tray, remains unchanged from the initial description.

The screenshot shows the Windows XP desktop with the Start menu open. The 'Control Panel' option is highlighted, and a tooltip window describes its function. 

New UI Elements:
- The Start menu is now visible.
- A tooltip window is present, displaying text that reads: "Provides options for you to customize the appearance and functionality of your computer, add or remove programs, and set up network connections and user accounts."

Missing UI Elements: None. 

Content Changes:
- The mouse cursor has moved from the center of the screen and is now hovering over the 'Control Panel' option in the Start menu.

The screenshot shows the Windows XP desktop with the Start menu open.  The "Rhizome" sub-menu, listing various programs like Internet Explorer and Control Panel, is also visible.

- The Start menu is now visible.
- The "Rhizome" sub-menu within the Start menu is visible.

The screenshot displays a standard Windows XP desktop with a solid blue background. The mouse cursor, represented by a white arrow, is hovering over the middle of the screen, indicating user interaction with the mouse.

- New UI Elements: The "Start" menu now displays a list of programs, folders, and system options such as "My Documents", "My Computer", "Control Panel", "All Programs", "Log Off", and "Turn off Computer". 
- Missing UI Elements: The "Start" button, previously described as the only visible element within the "Start" menu, is no longer the only element present.

The screenshot displays the Windows XP Start Menu, overlaid on the desktop. The user's mouse cursor, a white arrow, hovers over an empty section of the blue desktop background.  The Start Menu displays a vertical list of commonly used programs on the left and shortcuts to system folders and utilities on the right.  At the bottom of the Start Menu are the "Log Off", "Turn Off Computer" buttons, and the "All Programs" option. The taskbar is visible at the bottom of the screen, featuring the "Start" button on the left, the system tray with icons on the right, and the current time displayed as 11:04 AM. The "Recycle Bin" icon rests on the desktop in the bottom right corner.
